00:18:54,570 --> 00:18:59,020
I even found out today that
I was allergic to one of the medicines.

286
00:19:02,970 --> 00:19:07,510
Because someone knows me very well.

287
00:19:09,098 --> 00:19:15,324
He's the one that I thought didn't care
about me, in the way that I cared about him.

288
00:19:16,682 --> 00:19:18,722
But actually he remembers every detail about me.

289
00:19:19,710 --> 00:19:22,370
You mean your brother, right?

290
00:19:24,292 --> 00:19:24,742
Yes.

291
00:19:25,630 --> 00:19:26,880
He's more special.

292
00:19:32,342 --> 00:19:34,262
You're going to tell me that...

293
00:19:51,449 --> 00:19:53,215
Am I doing too much?

294
00:19:54,730 --> 00:19:56,400
I'm too deliberate,
right? So it's not destiny.

295
00:19:57,870 --> 00:19:58,310
Yes.

296
00:19:58,850 --> 00:20:00,690
It probably wasn't meant to be.

297
00:20:08,101 --> 00:20:09,001
Plearn.

298
00:20:10,676 --> 00:20:11,886
Don't be silent like this.

299
00:20:14,900 --> 00:20:17,950
I'm managing my feelings

300
00:20:18,430 --> 00:20:19,680
about what I need to do next.

301
00:20:20,980 --> 00:20:22,390
I was just heartbroken for the first time.

302
00:20:23,230 --> 00:20:24,530
I'm in a dilemma.

303
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:35,980
Keep fighting, heart.

304
00:20:36,780 --> 00:20:39,130
Your owner is a very nice person.

305
00:20:40,180 --> 00:20:42,140
He must definitely meet someone better than me.

306
00:20:43,460 --> 00:20:45,730
But you have to be patient during this time.

307
00:20:46,730 --> 00:20:48,170
I know you can get through it.

308
00:20:52,040 --> 00:20:52,970
You're...

309
00:20:53,640 --> 00:20:54,940
You broke my heart

310
00:20:55,480 --> 00:20:56,980
and still being cute towards me.

311
00:20:58,431 --> 00:20:59,331
You're bad.

312
00:20:59,370 --> 00:21:00,310
So bad.

313
00:21:01,820 --> 00:21:03,020
I'm sorry.

314
00:21:04,550 --> 00:21:05,560
You don't need to feel guilty about me.

315
00:21:06,790 --> 00:21:08,310
I can manage my feelings.

316
00:21:09,700 --> 00:21:11,390
I will be responsible for all my feelings.

317
00:21:12,300 --> 00:21:13,340
You don't need to worry about it.

318
00:21:27,700 --> 00:21:29,000
That friend

319
00:21:29,760 --> 00:21:31,750
looks really worried about you, right?

320
00:21:32,890 --> 00:21:36,380
When he told me that he went to the hospital
and couldn't find you,

321
00:21:36,770 --> 00:21:39,030
he came to wait for you at home.

322
00:21:40,787 --> 00:21:42,801
Is he the person you met at the food court?

323
00:21:48,924 --> 00:21:50,184
Did he...

324
00:21:51,459 --> 00:21:52,509
really flirt with you?

325
00:21:56,189 --> 00:21:58,499
What do you think, Park?

326
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:03,400
Park didn't say anything about it.

327
00:22:06,070 --> 00:22:08,640
Aren't you jealous of him a bit?

328
00:22:08,870 --> 00:22:09,640
I'm not jealous of him.

329
00:22:11,601 --> 00:22:13,341
But I'm not giving him to him.

330
00:22:13,480 --> 00:22:14,850
You kept saying that he was flirting with you.

331
00:22:14,850 --> 00:22:15,740
Why do you say it?

332
00:22:16,300 --> 00:22:17,240
He's flirting with you, so what's next?

333
00:22:17,470 --> 00:22:18,640
You will like him?

334
00:22:19,270 --> 00:22:20,200
I'm not giving you to him.

335
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:22,360
I cherished him for a long time.

336
00:22:23,120 --> 00:22:24,680
How can I give him to someone else?

337
00:22:26,130 --> 00:22:27,240
Who does he think he is?

338
00:22:27,780 --> 00:22:28,610
Call him here!

339
00:22:28,910 --> 00:22:29,900
Let's talk clearly.

340
00:22:31,190 --> 00:22:33,710
That day you said it was up to me.

341
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:36,880
My brain couldn't figure out how I had to respond.

342
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:39,790
At that time I still didn't
know how to process things.

343
00:22:41,347 --> 00:22:45,327
If you don't think it through,
you could've told me a couple days later.

344
00:22:45,860 --> 00:22:46,970
I always wait for you.

345
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:50,190
The way you say that makes me sad.

346
00:22:51,180 --> 00:22:53,160
You don't think I'm being sarcastic towards you?

347
00:22:54,222 --> 00:22:57,502
Does my face look pleased with you?

348
00:22:57,620 --> 00:22:58,050
Huh?

349
00:23:00,090 --> 00:23:02,330
Your face is always the same.

350
00:23:02,820 --> 00:23:04,000
How do I know?

351
00:23:11,462 --> 00:23:12,442
Is it flowing yet?

352
00:23:13,020 --> 00:23:13,560
Huh?

353
00:23:14,830 --> 00:23:18,830
Has your heart grown to love someone else?
And if it's already flowing?

354
00:23:22,670 --> 00:23:23,790
If it's already flowing.

355
00:23:31,030 --> 00:23:35,120
I'm worried about you until I'm about to cry.

356
00:23:45,210 --> 00:23:46,000
Park.

357
00:23:46,290 --> 00:23:46,860
Hmm?

358
00:23:47,680 --> 00:23:48,880
Do you love me?

359
00:23:49,270 --> 00:23:49,940
Yes.

360
00:23:51,230 --> 00:23:52,900
You answer me just like this?

361
00:23:54,810 --> 00:23:55,860
I just love you.

362
00:23:56,290 --> 00:23:57,570
Will you let me deny it?

363
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:01,880
You love me like a brother,

364
00:24:05,750 --> 00:24:07,470
do you love me like that?

365
00:24:09,483 --> 00:24:11,417
I thought so at first.

366
00:24:12,186 --> 00:24:13,256
But it's not.

367
00:24:15,380 --> 00:24:22,210
I think we are brothers. So I can't
imagine how we could love each other.

368
00:24:23,920 --> 00:24:24,960
Before,

369
00:24:26,510 --> 00:24:28,450
I never had feelings for you like this.

370
00:24:30,590 --> 00:24:31,910
A brother is a brother.

371
00:24:32,240 --> 00:24:33,540
How can I have more feelings for you?

372
00:24:36,770 --> 00:24:38,900
But as you grow up,

373
00:24:39,780 --> 00:24:40,770
everything changes.

374
00:24:45,890 --> 00:24:49,800
You suddenly become prettier.

375
00:24:53,650 --> 00:24:57,750
Suddenly my heart
fluttered because of you.

376
00:24:59,861 --> 00:25:07,981
I suddenly want to hug you like a lover.

377
00:25:09,560 --> 00:25:11,060
When I had feelings for you,

378
00:25:12,950 --> 00:25:15,860
I realized that I was in trouble.

379
00:25:17,892 --> 00:25:20,102
Because we grew up together.

380
00:25:22,090 --> 00:25:25,550
So I don't know if we
can really love each other.

381
00:25:28,612 --> 00:25:34,182
So I don't know if the two
of us can really get married

382
00:25:34,490 --> 00:25:37,060
like you ask every day.

383
00:25:39,030 --> 00:25:44,220
So I said I didn't understand
what marriage meant.

384
00:25:45,770 --> 00:25:49,920
My brain is always in
conflict with my heart.

385
00:25:51,720 --> 00:25:52,910
I'm afraid

386
00:25:54,290 --> 00:25:57,200
we're both doing something wrong.

387
00:26:14,710 --> 00:26:20,800
So I try to tell and try to make you stop
having feelings for me.

388
00:26:22,310 --> 00:26:23,380
And me too.

389
00:26:24,690 --> 00:26:27,730
I have to think that today it's good.

390
00:26:35,482 --> 00:26:36,012
Park.

391
00:26:36,120 --> 00:26:36,670
Look at this.

392
00:26:37,119 --> 00:26:38,589
I got a lot of roses.

393
00:26:38,670 --> 00:26:40,260
And then I got candy too.

394
00:26:40,510 --> 00:26:41,590
Look at this lollipop.

395
00:26:42,390 --> 00:26:43,280
Am I hot?

396
00:26:45,040 --> 00:26:45,970
You're ridiculous.

397
00:26:49,520 --> 00:26:50,800
I'll give you a rose. Do you want it?

398
00:26:51,660 --> 00:26:52,480
No.

399
00:26:53,818 --> 00:26:54,478
Here's all of them.

400
00:26:56,504 --> 00:26:57,444
Just go take a shower.

401
00:27:02,620 --> 00:27:06,470
I must have hurt your
feelings a lot in the past.

402
00:27:09,330 --> 00:27:10,790
You're right...

403
00:27:12,301 --> 00:27:13,481
but I can endure it.

404
00:27:15,850 --> 00:27:18,160
I'm mean to make you stop
you from having feelings for me,

405
00:27:19,100 --> 00:27:20,520
why do you have to endure it?

406
00:27:29,970 --> 00:27:33,660
You are worthy enough
to make me endure it.

407
00:27:35,570 --> 00:27:36,440
Park.

408
00:27:36,610 --> 00:27:37,130
Hmm?

409
00:27:38,510 --> 00:27:41,070
Can you say you
love me nicely for once?

410
00:27:45,920 --> 00:27:47,490
I love you, babe.

411
00:27:56,450 --> 00:28:00,800
The way you say this can kill me.

412
00:28:03,970 --> 00:28:06,730
You were the one who made the first move.

413
00:28:07,520 --> 00:28:10,430
Being that I'm serious,
does it make you die?

414
00:28:12,670 --> 00:28:14,510
Why do you have to
say that I'm a total flirt?

415
00:28:14,670 --> 00:28:15,750
It's a fact.

416
00:28:16,470 --> 00:28:18,030
You seduce me every day.

417
00:28:18,440 --> 00:28:20,240
How much do you think I can endure?

418
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:20,940
Huh?

419
00:28:22,170 --> 00:28:23,510
But you can endure it.

420
00:28:24,670 --> 00:28:26,470
You keep looking to kick me every day.

421
00:28:31,590 --> 00:28:34,200
Have I really kicked you once?

422
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:35,850
Huh?

423
00:29:05,350 --> 00:29:07,220
Until you know your feelings...

424
00:29:09,590 --> 00:29:11,290
You'd rather make me wait a long time.

425
00:29:26,320 --> 00:29:27,230
Are you teasing me?

426
00:29:28,030 --> 00:29:28,850
Why?

427
00:29:29,330 --> 00:29:29,950
Why?

428
00:29:30,730 --> 00:29:31,290
Why?

429
00:29:31,930 --> 00:29:32,800
Are you fluttering?

430
00:29:37,110 --> 00:29:39,290
Here, cold water.

431
00:29:40,730 --> 00:29:41,980
Thank you.

432
00:29:42,840 --> 00:29:43,550
Bie.

433
00:29:44,550 --> 00:29:47,500
Where did Kana's family go?

434
00:29:48,710 --> 00:29:51,530
Oh, Aunt Mam goes to practice Dharma.

435
00:29:51,880 --> 00:29:54,940
Aunt Kai was drunk at his friend's house as usual.

436
00:29:56,550 --> 00:29:57,080
Oh?

437
00:29:57,080 --> 00:29:59,080
What about Kana?

438
00:29:59,760 --> 00:30:01,080
He went with his mother.

439
00:30:01,378 --> 00:30:02,928
Kana went to the temple?

440
00:30:03,360 --> 00:30:03,760
Yeah.

441
00:30:03,930 --> 00:30:06,070
A monster like him can enter the temple?

442
00:30:07,537 --> 00:30:10,477
He was unusually good these days.

443
00:30:10,562 --> 00:30:13,052
He waits to make merit
and gives alms to monks in the morning.

444
00:30:13,527 --> 00:30:16,587
I think he might ordain next year.

445
00:30:17,138 --> 00:30:17,868
Ordain?

446
00:30:18,551 --> 00:30:22,611
I can't imagine Kana as a monk.

447
00:30:22,919 --> 00:30:23,709
Yes.

448
00:30:23,953 --> 00:30:25,063
Me too.

449
00:30:26,357 --> 00:30:29,442
From Kana (Kale) to carrots
(The colour of monk garbs)?

450
00:30:35,950 --> 00:30:37,290
It's just water here.

451
00:30:38,362 --> 00:30:39,912
Shall we go buy some bubble tea?

452
00:30:40,140 --> 00:30:41,720
Hey, okay!

453
00:30:42,283 --> 00:30:43,093
Would you like to go with us, Park?

454
00:30:43,645 --> 00:30:44,815
Okay.

455
00:30:45,500 --> 00:30:46,480
Come on.

456
00:30:51,769 --> 00:30:52,779
Jumbo!

457
00:30:53,730 --> 00:30:54,240
Hey.

458
00:30:54,690 --> 00:30:55,580
You puppy.

459
00:30:55,720 --> 00:30:56,910
You scared me.

460
00:30:57,170 --> 00:30:57,630
Hey.

461
00:30:58,130 --> 00:30:59,630
You always tease me.

462
00:30:59,630 --> 00:31:00,080
Huh?

463
00:31:03,120 --> 00:31:04,560
What's wrong with you?
Why are you holding my hand?

464
00:31:05,010 --> 00:31:07,200
Is your sleep normal?

465
00:31:07,320 --> 00:31:09,420
It's normal.

466
00:31:09,445 --> 00:31:10,035
Why?

467
00:31:10,060 --> 00:31:12,690
Are you still smoking?

468
00:31:13,380 --> 00:31:14,410
Sometimes.

469
00:31:14,718 --> 00:31:16,348
Are you still drinking alcohol?

470
00:31:16,910 --> 00:31:17,720
Yeah.

471
00:31:17,720 --> 00:31:18,790
All the time. Why?

472
00:31:19,330 --> 00:31:20,910
You haven't had any strange
symptoms lately, have you?

473
00:31:20,970 --> 00:31:22,360
No, I'm fine.

474
00:31:22,530 --> 00:31:23,610
But you are a strange person.

475
00:31:23,710 --> 00:31:24,880
What's wrong with you?

476
00:31:25,050 --> 00:31:27,370
Are you worried that
people won't know you're a nurse?

477
00:31:28,430 --> 00:31:30,560
You check my pulse.

478
00:31:30,750 --> 00:31:31,350
Bie.

479
00:31:31,617 --> 00:31:32,037
Oh...

480
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:32,970
Oh!

481
00:31:32,970 --> 00:31:34,250
It looks like it's going to rain today, right?

482
00:31:34,275 --> 00:31:35,305
It looks like it's going to rain.

483
00:31:35,794 --> 00:31:37,204
So sunny.

484
00:31:37,897 --> 00:31:38,617
Bie.

485
00:31:38,987 --> 00:31:41,337
How did Uncle Manop tell you?

486
00:31:42,012 --> 00:31:45,092
About the debt with Uncle Montri.

487
00:31:45,397 --> 00:31:46,347
What?

488
00:31:47,961 --> 00:31:50,561
Your father borrowed
money from Uncle Montri.

489
00:31:51,100 --> 00:31:53,110
I heard that your father
took the land as collateral.

490
00:31:53,830 --> 00:31:55,580
It looks like Uncle Montri
needs money lately.

491
00:31:55,580 --> 00:31:57,400
So he will sell that plot of land.

492
00:31:58,670 --> 00:32:00,710
I never knew about this before.

493
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:03,670
Your father didn't tell you anything?

494
00:32:06,420 --> 00:32:07,830
Since when?

495
00:32:08,610 --> 00:32:09,630
When...

496
00:32:11,250 --> 00:32:15,680
Since your father sent you to study abroad.

497
00:32:16,930 --> 00:32:19,720
Your father has been using the land
as collateral for 6-7 years.

498
00:32:21,740 --> 00:32:22,570
Let's go back.

499
00:32:24,190 --> 00:32:25,680
Jumbo, I have to go.

500
00:32:28,110 --> 00:32:29,120
Dad!

501
00:32:29,190 --> 00:32:30,120
Dad!

502
00:32:30,350 --> 00:32:31,250
Dad!

503
00:32:31,360 --> 00:32:33,120
Pyrin, where is our dad?

504
00:32:37,640 --> 00:32:38,770
Dad!

505
00:32:40,310 --> 00:32:41,570
Uncle Manop!

506
00:32:41,570 --> 00:32:42,290
Dad!

507
00:32:42,320 --> 00:32:43,200
Uncle Manop!

508
00:32:43,200 --> 00:32:44,510
What?

509
00:32:45,130 --> 00:32:46,250
What are you guys doing here?

510
00:32:46,830 --> 00:32:49,040
It's already evening,
why aren't you home yet?

511
00:32:49,130 --> 00:32:51,440
I thought you fainted to death at the farm.

512
00:32:51,465 --> 00:32:52,075
Hey.

513
00:32:52,409 --> 00:32:53,909
Is that your mouth?

514
00:32:54,450 --> 00:32:56,400
Why haven't you come back home yet?

515
00:32:56,650 --> 00:32:58,110
Can you see that my work is not finished yet?

516
00:32:58,160 --> 00:32:59,380
Why are you making me hurry?

517
00:32:59,610 --> 00:33:01,660
We need to talk, dad.

518
00:33:03,130 --> 00:33:05,460
Why then do you have to borrow other people's money?

519
00:33:05,530 --> 00:33:08,440
If you tell me one time that you don't have money,

520
00:33:08,540 --> 00:33:09,710
I would've never gone to study.

521
00:33:10,520 --> 00:33:12,040
I saw that you wanted to go there.

522
00:33:12,500 --> 00:33:15,530
It's a pity if you pass the exam
but don't have any money.

523
00:33:15,910 --> 00:33:17,580
And you seem happy.

524
00:33:18,020 --> 00:33:19,460
What do you want me to do?

525
00:33:19,750 --> 00:33:21,840
Just because of my happiness?

526
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:24,140
You must use the
land to pay off the debt.

527
00:33:24,150 --> 00:33:25,360
Is it the right thing, dad?

528
00:33:25,360 --> 00:33:26,270
Of course.

529
00:33:26,555 --> 00:33:30,445
How am I going to be your father
if I can't do little things for you?

530
00:33:31,199 --> 00:33:33,709
Okay, I'll pay the debt for you.

531
00:33:34,200 --> 00:33:34,920
You don't have to do it.

532
00:33:35,240 --> 00:33:36,410
What?

533
00:33:36,990 --> 00:33:38,020
Just keep your money.

534
00:33:38,790 --> 00:33:40,320
Use that money to make your future.

535
00:33:40,730 --> 00:33:42,160
You don't have to pay debts for me.

536
00:33:42,870 --> 00:33:44,850
Why can't I pay off your debt?

537
00:33:45,080 --> 00:33:47,010
Isn't this debt from me?

538
00:33:47,050 --> 00:33:48,770
You think I don't have money.

539
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:50,710
So you have a lot of money?

540
00:33:50,870 --> 00:33:51,370
Huh?

541
00:33:52,200 --> 00:33:55,550
I told you that I can work
and earn money every day.

542
00:33:55,850 --> 00:33:59,000
You kept telling me to take the civil service exam.

543
00:33:59,420 --> 00:34:01,310
I just want you to have a great future.

544
00:34:01,650 --> 00:34:03,790
I don't want you to be a farmer like me.

545
00:34:04,210 --> 00:34:06,570
Just doing good work to make money.

546
00:34:06,800 --> 00:34:08,000
It's for your life.

547
00:34:08,950 --> 00:34:10,890
Just talk about it later

548
00:34:11,045 --> 00:34:13,731
about this country
where there are many jobs

549
00:34:13,755 --> 00:34:16,440
other than civil servants
that can earn money.

550
00:34:17,070 --> 00:34:21,370
But now you should give money
back to Uncle Montri first.

551
00:34:22,260 --> 00:34:23,570
But it's your money.

552
00:34:24,356 --> 00:34:26,846
I can do anything with my money.

553
00:34:26,982 --> 00:34:32,232
Or you must not complain to me
if I pay for idols or expenses after this.

554
00:34:32,257 --> 00:34:33,457
Because it's my money.

555
00:34:34,013 --> 00:34:35,623
You're really complicated.

556
00:34:36,300 --> 00:34:37,620
It's a fact, isn't it?

557
00:34:38,263 --> 00:34:40,196
You kept forcing me to
take the civil service exam.

558
00:34:40,345 --> 00:34:42,278
Civil service jobs are
not suitable for everyone.

559
00:34:42,958 --> 00:34:43,728
Yes, uncle.

560
00:34:44,474 --> 00:34:46,224
Don't let Bie be like Pao.

561
00:34:47,160 --> 00:34:49,200
I don't have a higher education like you guys.

562
00:34:49,680 --> 00:34:51,710
I don't know what job is stable.

563
00:34:52,400 --> 00:34:57,970
An old man like me knows only good
and right civil service work.

564
00:34:58,964 --> 00:35:00,884
You use sad words with me.

565
00:35:01,260 --> 00:35:02,280
It's good for you.

566
00:35:03,464 --> 00:35:04,824
I'm grown up.

567
00:35:05,440 --> 00:35:07,040
You should stop complaining to me.

568
00:35:07,080 --> 00:35:09,910
The fact that I like Korean idols,

569
00:35:10,500 --> 00:35:14,810
even you put Tata
Young's posters on the wall.

570
00:35:15,150 --> 00:35:19,700
Don't think I don't remember
you liking singers either.

571
00:35:19,700 --> 00:35:21,180
You still remember it.

572
00:35:35,880 --> 00:35:36,520
Bie.

573
00:35:39,050 --> 00:35:43,650
I'm sorry that I always ended
up being a point of comparison.

574
00:35:44,126 --> 00:35:45,696
Actually, you didn't do anything wrong.

575
00:35:45,721 --> 00:35:47,511
I'm just born with perfection.

576
00:35:48,410 --> 00:35:50,290
I'm not as good as you think.

577
00:35:51,990 --> 00:35:54,830
And I'm not as good as other people think.

578
00:35:59,790 --> 00:36:06,690
Hey, I think now my dad knows that
my career can earn money.

579
00:36:08,632 --> 00:36:11,512
I just realized how rich you are.

580
00:36:11,537 --> 00:36:14,167
I don't go anywhere every day.
I rarely travel anywhere.

581
00:36:14,400 --> 00:36:16,290
Also, my father never asked me for money.

582
00:36:16,750 --> 00:36:19,450
He kept telling me to save money.
So I have some savings.

583
00:36:20,076 --> 00:36:21,276
Your dad loves you.

584
00:36:21,700 --> 00:36:22,700
I know.

585
00:36:24,960 --> 00:36:26,330
I love him too.

586
00:36:27,470 --> 00:36:30,950
But sometimes he messes with me too much.

587
00:36:31,900 --> 00:36:38,490
But now I know that he gave everything to me.

588
00:36:38,817 --> 00:36:40,237
He traded land

589
00:36:41,220 --> 00:36:42,680
to make me happy.

590
00:36:43,860 --> 00:36:46,690
I'm speechless.

591
00:36:48,665 --> 00:36:51,195
Even though he's not my real father.

592
00:36:51,220 --> 00:36:51,670
Huh?

593
00:36:53,385 --> 00:36:53,985
Oh.

594
00:36:54,283 --> 00:36:55,243
You were born late, right?

595
00:36:56,610 --> 00:36:58,360
Park never told you about it?

596
00:36:59,850 --> 00:37:03,910
My mom and he got married when I was a kid.

597
00:37:04,860 --> 00:37:07,010
But she died before.

598
00:37:07,550 --> 00:37:09,680
So my dad has always raised me since then.

599
00:37:10,380 --> 00:37:12,960
He really didn't need
to be go so hard to raise me.

600
00:37:15,923 --> 00:37:17,523
I want to make him proud.

601
00:37:18,033 --> 00:37:18,603
But...

602
00:37:19,473 --> 00:37:22,133
I want to be successful in my own way.

603
00:37:22,835 --> 00:37:25,625
And I will repay him in my ways.

604
00:37:27,416 --> 00:37:29,066
You are doing it right now.

605
00:37:41,680 --> 00:37:42,420
Park.

606
00:37:42,720 --> 00:37:43,250
Huh?

607
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:48,370
Have you ever thought about what
job you want me to do in the future?

608
00:37:49,060 --> 00:37:51,220
You have to think about it yourself.

609
00:37:52,990 --> 00:37:56,430
I don't even know what I want to do.

610
00:37:57,780 --> 00:37:59,140
What I'm good at.

611
00:38:00,450 --> 00:38:02,270
What I can do well.

612
00:38:03,210 --> 00:38:04,530
I really don't know.

613
00:38:05,620 --> 00:38:07,570
I'm a very normal person.

614
00:38:08,900 --> 00:38:10,770
I'm so normal that I can't find my true self.

615
00:38:12,260 --> 00:38:14,720
If I don't achieve anything.

616
00:38:16,360 --> 00:38:18,440
If I can't make you proud.

617
00:38:18,560 --> 00:38:20,640
Have I ever scolded you for this reason?

618
00:38:21,500 --> 00:38:22,330
No.

619
00:38:23,040 --> 00:38:27,100
The person who says
you're not good is yourself.

620
00:38:29,430 --> 00:38:31,360
If you don't know what you want to be,

621
00:38:33,210 --> 00:38:34,480
just slowly think about it.

622
00:38:35,900 --> 00:38:38,590
Success doesn't have to be great.

623
00:38:39,620 --> 00:38:41,020
Just do what you want to do.

624
00:38:42,130 --> 00:38:43,600
Just do what you like.

625
00:38:44,000 --> 00:38:45,340
You don't have to think
about whether I like it or not.

626
00:38:46,320 --> 00:38:48,030
I still fully support you anyway.

627
00:38:55,240 --> 00:38:56,600
If you are not good yet.

628
00:38:57,180 --> 00:38:59,190
If it's not good,
you just make it better.

629
00:39:00,130 --> 00:39:02,610
But if you keep saying you're not good

630
00:39:03,150 --> 00:39:04,480
and doing nothing,

631
00:39:04,890 --> 00:39:05,800
I'll scold you.

632
00:39:07,170 --> 00:39:08,080
Okay.

633
00:39:08,820 --> 00:39:09,980
I will try harder.

634
00:39:10,710 --> 00:39:11,190
Yeah.

635
00:39:12,550 --> 00:39:16,072
Actually, you're not normal.

636
00:39:25,810 --> 00:39:27,040
For me,

637
00:39:28,110 --> 00:39:29,860
you are a special one.
